CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "A Moving Family - Mrs. Evelyn Thomas and her family of five (the youngest is not shown) have moved from one hovel to another five times just ahead of the redevelopers' power shovels. They have lived in two places where disastrous fires occurred shortly after they moved out. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Evelyn Thomas and her children posed on steps of their home in Ingram Palace housing project, Ingram, Pennsylvania
